To create a simple HTML page, you need to write the HTML code and save it with the .html extension. Here's a basic template for an HTML page:

Basic HTML Template:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Simple HTML Page</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        h1 {
            color: #333;
        }
        p {
            color: #555;
        }
        .container {
            width: 80%;
            margin: 0 auto;
            background-color: #fff;
            padding: 20px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <div class="container">
        <h1>Welcome to My HTML Page</h1>
        <p>This is a simple webpage created with HTML. You can add more content here.</p>
        <p>HTML is the standard markup language for creating web pages.</p>
    </div>

</body>
</html>

Explanation:

1. <!DOCTYPE html>: Declares the document type and version of HTML (HTML5 here).


2. <html lang="en">: Defines the language of the page (English).


3. <head>: Contains metadata like character set, viewport settings, and the title of the page.


4. <style>: Internal CSS to style the page (you can also link to an external CSS file).


5. <body>: Contains the content of the page. Inside it, thereâ€™s a div container that holds the heading (<h1>) and paragraphs (<p>).



Steps to view your page:

1. Open a text editor (such as Notepad, VS Code, or Sublime Text).


2. Copy and paste the above code into the editor.


3. Save the file with the .html extension (e.g., index.html).


4. Open the file in a web browser to view your page.



This is just a starting point, and you can expand the HTML with more features such as images, links, forms, etc. Let me know if you need more advanced examples!

